cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the classification of text documents, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of low-dimensional feature space and statistics for prediction, which is related to machine learning (ML) and data mining. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second likely category. The paper also mentions the use of TF-IDF, which is a common technique in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which is related to artificial intelligence (AI) and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with data stream applications, which is related to the field of stream processing and could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
